How to Run the Code

1. Install Required Dependencies

Make sure you have Python 3.11, PySpark, and Java JDK 17 installed. If PySpark is not installed, run:

pip install pyspark

2. Run the PySpark Job

Navigate to the directory containing app.py and execute:

python3 app.py ./data/dict.txt ./data/articles.txt ./good_articles ./bad_articles

3. Expected Output
	•	The script reads dict.txt and articles.txt.
	•	It filters out empty articles.
	•	It classifies articles into:
	•	Good Articles (≤30% misspellings) → saved in good_articles/
	•	Bad Articles (>30% misspellings) → saved in bad_articles/
	•	The results are stored in text files in the output folders.
